// @test regression/INV016-union-arg-validation
// @description Union-typed params (nz's series int/float/color, int's series int/float) were skipped by the arg checker (a union maps to "unknown"), so nz(<bool>) and int(true) - real CE10123 errors in TV - slipped through. INV016 validates the arg's base against the union's member set when the arg is reliably typed; INV085 aligns the diagnostic with TV's CE10123 template. See investigations/INV016-union-arg-validation/notes.md and investigations/INV085-union-arg-ce10123-template/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=3, message=/Cannot call "nz" with argument "source"="call "operator >" \(series bool\)"/
// @expects error: line=4, message=/Cannot call "int" with argument "x"="true"/
//@version=6
indicator("INV016 union-arg validation")
plot(nz(close > open) ? 1 : 0)
x = int(true)
plot(x)
